B.  National Consultants 
4.  Research officer (24 person-months). The research officer will have at least 2 years of 
experience in assisting the conduct of applied economics research, preferably on regional 
cooperation. The research officer will provide technical and administrative support for activities 
to be implemented under the TA. Responsibilities will include the following: 
(i)  assist the research director in the conduct of tasks; 
(ii)  provide secretariat and coordination support for all CAREC Institute knowledge 
activities, including organizing and updating TA information and data; 
(iii)  help prepare progress reports on the CAREC Institute; 
(iv)  help review drafts of knowledge products; 
(v)  help identify knowledge products to include in the CAREC Institute databases; 
(vi)  organize knowledge events;  
(vii)  develop own areas of research in accordance with CAREC Institute work plan;  
(viii)  conduct research on any issue in the CAREC Institute medium-term research 
agenda; 
(ix)  carry out other related tasks as requested by the team leader; and 
(x)  submit quarterly reports on tasks performed during the assignment. 

5.   Database  and website  analyst  (24 person-months). The analyst will have at least 
2 years of work experience in designing, developing, and maintaining large databases and 
similar web-based programs and applications. Responsibilities will include the following: 
(i)  develop and maintain databases to serve as repositories of knowledge products 
to be generated and collected under the CAREC Institute; 
(ii)  coordinate with the specialists responsible for maintaining the CAREC website to 
ensure that the CAREC Institute section contains updated information and allows 
access to selected sections of the institute‘s databases; 
(iii)  design and develop an online knowledge portal to facilitate virtual exchange of 
knowledge  among  key  stakeholders,  as  well  as  researchers  and  academics 
interested in high-priority CAREC concerns; 
(iv)  ensure  security  and  reliability  of  the  CAREC  Institute‘s  databases  and 
information technology systems;  
(v)  carry out other related tasks as requested by the team leader; and  
(vi)  submit quarterly reports on the tasks performed during the assignment. 

6.   Program  coordinator (24 person-months). The program coordinator will have work 
experience in development banking and/or regional cooperation programs and initiatives. The 
program coordinator will be engaged to support and coordinate knowledge-related events and 
assist in all administrative activities. Responsibilities will include the following: 
(i)  provide  logistical  support  and  other  related  arrangements  in  organizing  and 
conducting knowledge initiatives, workshops, conferences, or seminars that will 
be held during TA implementation; 
(ii)  provide secretariat and coordination support, together with research officer, for all 
CAREC Institute knowledge activities; 
(iii)  ensure  smooth  flow  of  documents  and  communication  between  relevant 
departments in ADB and the resident missions; and 
  (iv)  carry out other related tasks as requested by the team leader.
